@node about "About mp3info"

mp3info is a little arexx for DOpus 5. It gives you information about mp3's
and plays them with Song Player or DeliTRacker.

@endnode
@node requirements Requirements

You need following things to use mp3info.      

- DOpus 5
- DeliTracker Or Song Player
- MP3Tool
- Installed ARexx system                                
- rexxsupport.library
@endnode

@node install Install

First of all you have to copy mp3infoDT.dopus5 or mp3infoSP.dopus5 (Depending
which version you are going to use. DT=Delitracker and SP=SongPlayer version)
to DOpus5:arexx/ Then you must edit the script a little bit. Just chance the
SongPlayer or Delitracker command-path to one that you use.

After that you may call it from the 'Double-click' function for
the 'Music, MPEG Layer3' filetype. Enter the following command:
<ARexx> DOpus5:arexx/mp3info??.dopus5 {f} (?? = DT=Delitracker and 
                                                SP=SongPlayer version)

@endnode
@node usage "Usage"

    After you have install it just double click mp3's and rest should be
quite self explanatory.

@endnode
